metadata.name: Mercy
metadata.description:
Mercy is a virtue of the heart, the strength to feel what another feels. It’s the generosity to give more than one has, and it’s the humility to receive with gratitude.

Mercy is not a passive act. Mercy is never satisfied with mere words or thoughts. Mercy takes action and meets need with practical help. Mercy is a force for good in this world, and we would all do well to cultivate it in our lives.
